Good catch! You are completely right. Because the raw data was broken down strictly into 30 days (which is mathematically about 4.5 weeks), I accidentally pushed the projects into an awkward "Week 5" slot. Standardizing it to a strict 4-week-per-month structure is much cleaner for the UI and much less confusing for the students. I have combined the foundational days and moved the projects into the 4th week of each month to keep it perfectly balanced. Here is the corrected, strictly 4-week Curriculum Builder text to copy-paste: ### 6. Curriculum Builder (Corrected 4-Week Structure) *Month 1 Title:* Data Foundations & Analysis * *Week 1 Title:* Python Basics & Structures * Topic: Intro to Data Science (Type: Live) * Topic: Python Setup & Basics (Type: Video) * Topic: Variables & Control Flow (Type: Live) * Topic: Functions & Modularity (Type: Live) * Topic: Lists, Tuples & Dicts (Type: Video) * *Week 2 Title:* NumPy & Pandas * Topic: Introduction to NumPy (Type: Live) * Topic: NumPy Advanced & Vectorized (Type: Live) * Topic: Pandas Introduction (Type: Video) * Topic: Data Cleaning Techniques (Type: Live) * Topic: Data Transformation (Type: Live) * *Week 3 Title:* EDA, SQL & Excel * Topic: Exploratory Data Analysis (Type: Live) * Topic: Data Visualization Basics (Type: Video) * Topic: SQL Basics & Aggregations (Type: Live) * Topic: Advanced SQL & Joins (Type: Live) * Topic: Excel & BI Tools (Type: Video) * *Week 4 Title:* Project 1 - Business Analysis * Topic: Data Cleaning & SQL Prep (Type: Project) * Topic: EDA & Visualization (Type: Project) * Topic: Dashboard Creation (Type: Project) * Topic: Presentation & Review (Type: Live) *Month 2 Title:* Statistics & Machine Learning * *Week 1 Title:* Statistics for Data Science * Topic: Descriptive Statistics (Type: Live) * Topic: Probability Concepts (Type: Video) * Topic: Inferential Statistics (Type: Live) * Topic: Hypothesis Testing (Type: Live) * Topic: Statistics Lab (Type: Project) * *Week 2 Title:* ML Foundations * Topic: Machine Learning Overview (Type: Video) * Topic: ML Workflow & Linear Regression (Type: Live) * Topic: Logistic Regression (Type: Live) * Topic: Model Evaluation (Type: Video) * *Week 3 Title:* Advanced ML * Topic: Decision Trees & Random Forest (Type: Live) * Topic: KNN & Distance Metrics (Type: Video) * Topic: Feature Engineering (Type: Live) * Topic: Hyperparameter Tuning (Type: Live) * *Week 4 Title:* Project 2 - Churn Prediction * Topic: Preprocessing & EDA (Type: Project) * Topic: Feature Engineering (Type: Project) * Topic: Model Building & Evaluation (Type: Project) * Topic: Business Recommendations (Type: Live) *Month 3 Title:* Advanced Analytics & Readiness * *Week 1 Title:* Advanced Topics * Topic: Time Series Basics (Type: Live) * Topic: Intro to NLP (Type: Live) * Topic: Handling Imbalanced Data (Type: Video) * Topic: Model Explainability (Type: Video) * Topic: Advanced Analytics Lab (Type: Project) * *Week 2 Title:* Deployment & MLOps * Topic: Model Deployment Concepts (Type: Video) * Topic: Flask / FastAPI Intro (Type: Live) * Topic: Version Control with Git (Type: Video) * Topic: MLOps Overview (Type: Live) * Topic: Deployment Lab (Type: Project) * *Week 3 Title:* Industry Capstone (Part 1) * Topic: Problem Framing & Setup (Type: Project) * Topic: Data Prep & Cleaning (Type: Project) * Topic: Advanced Modeling Phase 1 (Type: Project) * *Week 4 Title:* Industry Capstone (Part 2) * Topic: Advanced Modeling Phase 2 (Type: Project) * Topic: Deployment Simulation (Type: Project) * Topic: Dashboard & Portfolio Push (Type: Project) * Topic: Executive Presentation (Type: Live) Would you like me to map out the final text for the "Admission Process" steps (Application, Counselling, Enrollment) next?
